name: ANCDT37
title: ANC.DT.37 Intimate partner violence (IPV) first-line support and treatment
description: Woman has been subjected to IPV

relatedArtifact.display: Value set Has the woman  been subjected to intimate partner violence

parameter.name: Should Provide first-line support. Four (4) kinds of needs deserve attention:– Immediate emotional/psychological health needs– Immediate physical health needs– Ongoing safety needs– Ongoing support and mental health needs.

Should Ask the following questions:  -Has the physical violence happened more often or gotten worse over the past 6 months? - Has he ever used a weapon or threatened you with a weapon? - Has he ever tried to strangle you? - Do you believe he could kill you? - Has he ever beaten you when you were pregnant? - Is he violently and constantly jealous of you?

Should If it is not safe for the woman to return home, make appropriate referrals for shelter or safe housing, or work with her to identify a safe place she can go to (such as a friend’s home or church).
